# =====================================================================
# SERRES DRIVE — .gitignore
# Rule of thumb: the repo holds ONLY what a browser actually requests.
# Everything else (original downloads, working folders, duplicates) stays
# local. Written BEFORE the first commit on purpose — once something is in
# git history it cannot be removed without rewriting that history, and
# Hostinger serves the repo root, so anything committed is also reachable
# from the live domain.
# =====================================================================

# --- System / editor -------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp

# Credentials. There are none today; the rule is preventive.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# --- Scrape working folder (do not publish) --------------------------
# sicurcars-scrape/ is research on a third party: RESUMEN.md documents how
# their Instagram was captured after a 401 anti-bot block and proposes a
# tool to finish the job; it also carries their business email and phone.
# media/ is a byte-identical duplicate of assets/img/cars/scrape/. No page
# on the site references any of it (grep "sicurcars-scrape" in html/css/js
# returns nothing), and Hostinger would expose it at /sicurcars-scrape/.
sicurcars-scrape/

# --- Original 3D model downloads -------------------------------------
# The four Sketchfab bundles are the raw material that assets/models/*.glb
# were built from. A .glb already embeds its textures and a browser cannot
# open a .rar, so this is 81 MB of dead weight — and redistributing a
# vendor source/ folder is what paid model licences typically forbid.
2020-audi-rs6-avant/
2020-mercedes-benz-g-class-amg-g63/
2023-bmw-m3-touring (1)/
porsche-gt3-rs (1)/

# In case a model is ever unpacked inside the repo.
*.rar
*.zip
*.7z
*.fbx
*.blend
*.usdz

# --- Loose videos at the root ----------------------------------------
# Animation tests no page references. The only video that plays is
# assets/img/hero.mp4 (js/app.js:353).
3d-animation-*.mp4

# --- Unused fleet photography ----------------------------------------
# assets/img/cars/sicurcars/ holds 31 unretouched copies that nothing
# requests — the site reads cars/<slug>.jpg and cars/ring/<slug>.jpg.
# They still show the SICURCARS plate, so they are the last thing that
# belongs in a public repo. Kept on disk as the originals.
assets/img/cars/sicurcars/

# --- Instagram posters: only the 15 actually displayed ---------------
# The folder is 134 MB, but js/media-map.js names just 15 .jpg files and
# js/car.js:228 renders them as <img> — there is no code path for video,
# so the 16 .mp4 files (128 MB) are requested by nobody.
# The whole folder is ignored and the 15 used files are re-admitted below.
# If you add a photo to media-map.js, add it HERE too with a leading "!".
assets/img/cars/scrape/*
!assets/img/cars/scrape/2026-01-30_DUIayrkjuP0.jpg
!assets/img/cars/scrape/2026-02-12_DUqzW7uDcaL.jpg
!assets/img/cars/scrape/2026-02-20_DU-RvxBDoDm.jpg
!assets/img/cars/scrape/2026-02-27_DVRT_hDjSAV.jpg
!assets/img/cars/scrape/2026-03-05_DVf902oDhL0.jpg
!assets/img/cars/scrape/2026-03-05_DVg0NxTDWMO.jpg
!assets/img/cars/scrape/2026-03-13_DV08YVODvdx.jpg
!assets/img/cars/scrape/2026-03-18_DWBjCCLjXtQ.jpg
!assets/img/cars/scrape/2026-04-10_DW9XTMvjaXY.jpg
!assets/img/cars/scrape/2026-04-15_DXKhJ8UDTKH.jpg
!assets/img/cars/scrape/2026-04-23_DXe_yzLDf4H.jpg
!assets/img/cars/scrape/2026-05-06_DYAeFsqjRWl.jpg
!assets/img/cars/scrape/2026-05-10_DYKxvRLDb-7.jpg
!assets/img/cars/scrape/2026-05-17_DYc8A-dN9E3.jpg
!assets/img/cars/scrape/2026-05-26_DY0Q91JN29-.jpg

# --- No build step here, but just in case ----------------------------
node_modules/
dist/
*.log
